    "update docs and push changes to git",
    "/plan \"in the apps/plugin project, for the site home-search-ca, when we do the data enrichment, the description contains multiple values separates by specific token string. Let's make new data objects to contain each new token string that we can then parse out later. We need to tokenize the different objects based on the starting token strings as they are all contained in a single string only separated by the tokens and the tokens always end with a ':'. The first token is always for the actual decription: 'About the property:', Then we would see 'Extra info:', then we would see 'House features:'.\". The extraInfo object will contain an array of strings separated by commas.",
    "/implement specs/hsc-description-tokenization.md",
    "Also the home-search-ca has its own 'Property Details' section which we will add as a new object to the enrichement output data object as hscPropertyDetails. Here is the html snippet we need to parse out the key value pairs. There is also a rooms section that list the level -> room name -> dimensions -> floor type. We need an hascRooms object as well.",
